                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 493.11/389.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">American Chargé d’Affaires</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-09-18">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 18, 1913</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Informs him, in reply to his No. 911, that the Government of the United States
                    does not contemplate presenting any claim for the expenses incurred in the
                    maintenance of troops in China during the revolution. Authorizes him to inform
                    his colleagues.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Osborne</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
